content:
As an AI language model, I don't have personal preferences. However, there are many pop songs that feature the saxophone that have become classics over time. Here are a few examples:

- "Careless Whisper" by George Michael
- "Baker Street" by Gerry Rafferty
- "Born to Run" by Bruce Springsteen
- "Always on My Mind" by Pet Shop Boys
- "Uptown Funk" by Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars
- "Who Can It Be Now?" by Men at Work
- "Just the Way You Are" by Billy Joel
- "Take Five" by Dave Brubeck Quartet (instrumental)
- "Tequila" by The Champs (instrumental)

These are just a few examples - there are countless other great pop songs that feature the saxophone!
